1
00:01:36,970 --> 00:01:40,110
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:43,210
[Episode 35]

3
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:44,570
Mr. Meng.

4
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:45,229
Mr. Meng.

5
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:45,930
Mr. Meng.

6
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,260
Come in.

7
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,450
Mr. Meng.

8
00:02:09,449 --> 00:02:10,190
Here is the list

9
00:02:10,190 --> 00:02:11,110
of new employees

10
00:02:11,110 --> 00:02:11,910
you asked for.

11
00:02:12,710 --> 00:02:13,490
Leave it there.

12
00:02:13,490 --> 00:02:14,690
I'll leave you alone.

13
00:02:26,510 --> 00:02:30,570
[Employee Registration Form]

14
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:33,690
[Employee information confirmed.
(Recommended by Bai Chun.)]

15
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:46,579
[Ordinary People on the Frontline
of Anti-Poaching in Bolamula]

16
00:03:06,090 --> 00:03:07,760
Bai, what's up?

17
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,550
Jiege Subdistrict Police Station—

18
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:10,600
come over now.

19
00:03:12,530 --> 00:03:13,530
Be quick.

20
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:15,190
We need to talk to you.

21
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,570
Hello.

22
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,410
Officer Bai asked me to come.

23
00:04:00,410 --> 00:04:00,940
This way.

24
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:03,190
You're here.

25
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:05,830
You've been drinking.

26
00:04:09,420 --> 00:04:10,020
You know why

27
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,020
I called you here?

28
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:19,850
Come with me.

29
00:04:21,820 --> 00:04:22,950
Is something wrong?

30
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:33,130
Is Wang Qiaoling your mother?

31
00:04:35,930 --> 00:04:36,720
Yes.

32
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:39,600
Come in.

33
00:04:42,659 --> 00:04:43,800
I'm not leaving!

34
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,880
I'm not leaving!

35
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:49,830
You have to help me

36
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:50,750
find that man.

37
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,840
I just want to ask him

38
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:54,750
why he lied to me.

39
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:56,500
Why? Why?

40
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:58,720
For the money in your account.

41
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,780
I don't believe it.

42
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:01,780
There are

43
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:03,430
so many of us in our dance team.

44
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:03,960
Why did he

45
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:05,810
specifically add me on WeChat?

46
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,240
He said

47
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,920
he fell for me at first sight.

48
00:05:08,130 --> 00:05:09,000
If I were a scammer,

49
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,730
I'd pick you at first sight too.

50
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:12,480
Out of all those old ladies,

51
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,390
I bet you were wearing

52
00:05:13,390 --> 00:05:14,100
the most jewelry,

53
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,160
weren't you?

54
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,070
Did that make you

55
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:18,270
dance half a beat slower
than everyone else?

56
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:20,050
He's actually got a bit of conscience.

57
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:20,820
He left

58
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:21,890
without taking that jade

59
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:22,920
off your neck.

60
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:23,340
Hey...

61
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,670
That's enough.

62
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:29,280
Alright, Mom.

63
00:05:30,150 --> 00:05:32,300
Cheer up, okay?

64
00:05:32,990 --> 00:05:34,050
I'll make up

65
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:35,510
for the money you lost.

66
00:05:35,510 --> 00:05:36,810
I want the man.

67
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,900
I just want to ask him to his face,

68
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,750
during the time

69
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:41,830
we spent together,

70
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:43,830
was every word he said to me

71
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:45,740
a lie?

72
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:47,840
You...

73
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:49,810
Why won't you wake up?

74
00:05:50,409 --> 00:05:51,650
This isn't love.

75
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,690
It's a scam!

76
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:53,659
Impossible!

77
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,830
What's wrong with me falling in love?

78
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,409
Fine. Let's go home now.

79
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,380
We'll just consider it

80
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:00,430
money spent on a lesson.

81
00:06:00,430 --> 00:06:00,980
Let's go.

82
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:01,860
Let's go home. Come on.

83
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:02,570
I'm not leaving!

84
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:03,330
Don't touch me!

85
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:03,680
Stop it.

86
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,150
I'm not leaving!

87
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:05,330
That's enough.

88
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:07,270
You've been scolding her
since you came in.

89
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:09,000
Why don't you look at yourself?

90
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,980
Many elderly people have been
scammed recently.

91
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:12,810
You think it's because

92
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:13,470
they're too trusting

93
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:15,200
and out of touch with the times.

94
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:15,830
But have you ever wondered

95
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:17,030
why they get scammed?

96
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:19,640
These elderly people

97
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,840
share a common trait.

98
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:22,560
Either they live alone

99
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:24,240
and their children are in other cities,

100
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,390
or their children are busy with work

101
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:25,970
all day

102
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,450
and don't have time for them.

103
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:27,930
You can't just

104
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:29,590
blame your mom for what happened.

105
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,320
You're responsible for it too.

106
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:35,670
Come on, Ms. Wang,

107
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:36,620
calm down.

108
00:06:37,220 --> 00:06:38,350
Let's go home, okay?

109
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:38,980
Okay.

110
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,560
Okay?

111
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,240
Careful.

112
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:56,860
Watch your step.

113
00:06:58,750 --> 00:06:59,850
Don't worry, Ms. Wang,

114
00:06:59,850 --> 00:07:00,720
we will

115
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:01,750
keep you updated.

116
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:04,340
Mom, you go up first.

117
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,380
I'll have a few more words
with Officer Bai.

118
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:06,790
Okay.

119
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:10,680
Bai, thank you.

120
00:07:11,140 --> 00:07:12,720
Now that we're friends on WeChat,

121
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,270
feel free to chat with me anytime.

122
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,220
Sure thing.

123
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:15,570
Okay.

124
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:16,580
Go on up, Ms. Wang.

125
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:17,660
I'll go up now.

126
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,120
Give me the bag.

127
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,530
Okay.

128
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:21,570
Watch your step.

129
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:30,800
Thank you.

130
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:32,750
Even driving us back.

131
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,390
No problem.

132
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:35,360
They called me over

133
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,730
because I'm familiar

134
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,310
with

135
00:07:37,330 --> 00:07:39,040
the suspect's background.

136
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,900
This guy is a repeat offender.

137
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:42,600
Having you handle

138
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,950
these trivial cases

139
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,960
is a waste of your talent.

140
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,490
How can you call them trivial?

141
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:50,800
All cases

142
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:51,950
are major cases.

143
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,430
For another family,

144
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:55,010
this could be

145
00:07:55,010 --> 00:07:57,010
a catastrophe that bankrupts them.

146
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:00,240
Just like Wu Jiang's death.

147
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:04,770
It might look like a simple

148
00:08:04,770 --> 00:08:05,830
traffic accident.

149
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:07,230
But for me,

150
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,450
it's not over yet.

151
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,780
Letting a case like this affect your work—

152
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,320
is it worth it?

153
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,360
It's not about whether
it's worth it or not.

154
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,490
Once you've seen it,

155
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,490
you can't pretend you haven't.

156
00:08:25,050 --> 00:08:26,110
That's the police.

157
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:34,750
Alright,

158
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,120
you should go up now.

159
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,059
I should go too.

160
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,340
I asked you to post

161
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:03,070
on Moments to make us official.

162
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:04,770
Look at this.

163
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:05,910
What does this post

164
00:09:05,910 --> 00:09:06,910
have to do with me?

165
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:15,460
Look.

166
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,290
Fine.

167
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:26,500
I'll forgive you this time.

168
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,480
I'll post one too.

169
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:31,240
I'm going to post it openly.

170
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,190
Let me tell you,

171
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:35,030
I've never shown off
my relationship before.

172
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:36,550
When I dated as a kid,

173
00:09:36,630 --> 00:09:37,810
it was like being a spy.

174
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:39,270
I had to hide it from my mom.

175
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:40,470
Back then,

176
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,360
Auntie Zhang opposed it

177
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:44,160
because she didn't want it to
affect your studies.

178
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,770
Now you don't have to hide it,

179
00:09:45,770 --> 00:09:47,170
but she still opposes it.

180
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:49,600
She's afraid it'll affect your future.

181
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,060
Who said my mom opposes it?

182
00:09:52,580 --> 00:09:53,150
Waiter.

183
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:54,670
Two Cokes, please.

184
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:55,000
Thanks.

185
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,330
Sure.

186
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:56,650
Cold one for me.

187
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:57,410
Okay.

188
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:58,510
Thanks.

189
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,180
I'm not stupid.

190
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,840
I can tell.

191
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,210
Don't worry.

192
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,680
I won't make things difficult for you.

193
00:10:11,130 --> 00:10:11,530
Here.

194
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:12,250
Thanks.

195
00:10:12,290 --> 00:10:12,790
Thanks.

196
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:18,800
What do you mean by that?

197
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:22,230
Are you getting cold feet?

198
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:25,650
If you don't back out, I won't either.

199
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:28,990
Here.

200
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,700
Eat up.

201
00:10:40,810 --> 00:10:41,210
Let's

202
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,450
go see a movie after we finish.

203
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:43,090
But

204
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:44,670
I don't watch action movies.

205
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:45,670
I don't like them.

206
00:10:46,330 --> 00:10:48,390
Anything with chasing and fighting.

207
00:10:49,590 --> 00:10:50,860
What are you laughing at?

208
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,100
I don't like them either.

209
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,270
You don't either?

210
00:10:53,860 --> 00:10:54,290
I thought

211
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:55,360
you liked that kind of stuff.

212
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,890
You look like you can fight.

213
00:10:57,170 --> 00:10:58,290
That's exactly why

214
00:10:58,410 --> 00:10:59,410
I don't like them.

215
00:11:00,130 --> 00:11:00,720
Movies are for fun,

216
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,800
aren't they?

217
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:05,030
To see things that aren't in reality.

218
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:08,340
Eat.

219
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,810
Don't answer it.

220
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:20,470
It's your day off, finally...

221
00:11:21,770 --> 00:11:22,240
Hello?

222
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:22,790
Hello?

223
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:23,480
Han.

224
00:11:23,610 --> 00:11:24,820
Where are you? Come back immediately.

225
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:25,420
The police

226
00:11:25,430 --> 00:11:27,160
are looking for you at the mine.

227
00:11:27,530 --> 00:11:28,530
Come back, quick.

228
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:29,970
What's wrong?

229
00:11:30,370 --> 00:11:33,250
[Criminal Police Brigade]

230
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:36,410
Shao.

231
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:39,010
Shao.

232
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:41,390
What's going on?

233
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,640
I was going to ask you.

234
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,370
Xinhai reported that they found

235
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,440
flammable and explosive materials

236
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,700
in Han Xuechao's dorm.

237
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,690
Captain Bai.

238
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:48,620
Captain Bai.

239
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:51,080
Over here. Let's talk here.

240
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:52,960
He already has a record.

241
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,000
A while ago,

242
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,450
he just caused a scene at Xinhai.

243
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:56,580
Xinhai suspects him

244
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,460
of plotting a security incident.

245
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,590
That's impossible.

246
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:01,020
Han has a short temper

247
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:02,000
and has issues with Xinhai,

248
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,700
but he knows

249
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:03,320
what he can

250
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:04,580
and cannot do.

251
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,370
The police said they need to

252
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:07,410
check the surveillance

253
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:07,950
to see

254
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:08,720
if the stuff was really

255
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,720
brought in by him.

256
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:11,910
I don't think

257
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:14,170
Han would do something like that either.

258
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,610
If they don't find anything,

259
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:18,150
how soon can he be released?

260
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:20,940
Illegally storing and transporting
hazardous materials—

261
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:22,150
detention for over five days

262
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,220
but less than ten.

263
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:26,960
Bai Ju—

264
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:28,900
Shao, don't be like this.

265
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:30,050
Since we were kids,

266
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:31,920
you use this tone when you're angry.

267
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,280
It gives me the creeps.

268
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:39,940
You used Han to investigate those things.

269
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,280
Now he's locked up.

270
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:43,570
And you're on leave

271
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,800
because of this case.

272
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,220
You need to weigh the consequences

273
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,100
of going on

274
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,390
investigating this.

275
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,270
You're a cop, so I won't interfere.

276
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:54,650
But I have to look out for Han Xuechao.

277
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:57,960
Shao,

278
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:00,730
you're serious about Han?

279
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,640
What kind of question is that?

280
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:04,890
When have I ever not been serious?

281
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:05,690
It's not that.

282
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:08,280
I just don't get it.

283
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:11,320
What do you see in Han?

284
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,640
You need a reason

285
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,600
to hate someone.

286
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:23,520
You also need a reason to love someone.

287
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:26,260
But you don't need that to like someone.

288
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:30,850
I don't quite understand.

289
00:13:31,460 --> 00:13:32,870
So at the moment,

290
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,700
you like Han,

291
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,070
and this is the first stage.

292
00:13:37,070 --> 00:13:38,600
So the second stage is love?

293
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:40,820
Can you really divide it like that?

294
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:43,720
Han

295
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:44,790
is a loyal

296
00:13:44,820 --> 00:13:45,770
and honest man.

297
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,530
Shao,

298
